-- Dubai's Emaar Properties shares surge before malls unit flotation
-- By Matt Smith
-- Sun Aug 31, 2014 02:17AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, Aug 31 (Reuters) - Shares in Dubai's Emaar Properties <EMAR.DU> jumped in early trade on Sunday after the developer said it would launch an initial public offer for its malls unit next month in what will be the emirate's largest share sale in recent years.

Emaar's shares rose 5.4 percent to 10.80 dirhams, bringing their year-to-date gains to 56 percent.  Ten analysts surveyed by Reuters have a median price target for the stock of 11.30 dirhams and a mean target of 10.83 dirhams. Seven rate the stock a "buy" or a "strong buy".